item.description:
So far, I had used the personal tokens method for authorizing myself against GitHub when working with private modules, but now I figured out how to make it work directly with Git and my SSH config already existing.
TL;DR;
1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 # vim ft=gitconfig # ~/.gitconfig [url &#34;ssh://git@github.com/nrxr&#34;] insteadOf = https://github.com/nrxr [url &#34;ssh://git@x.github.com/employer&#34;] insteadOf = https://github.com/employer 1 2 3 4 5 6 # vim ft=sshconfig # ~/.
